\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Here\u8217\'92s where you stop believing me.\u8221\'94 The little fellow was sicker than he looked. \u8220\'93A man who deals with dreams both awake and sleeping isn\u8217\'92t too concerned with belief and disbelief, Mr. Orr. They\u8217\'92re not categories I use much. They don\u8217\'92t apply. So ignore that, and go on. I\u8217\'92m interested.\u8221\'94 Did that sound patronizing? He looked at Orr to see if the statement had been taken amiss, and met, for one instant, the man\u8217\'92s eyes. Extraordinarily beautiful eyes, Haber thought, and was surprised by the word, for beauty was not a category he used much either. The irises were blue or gray, very clear, as if transparent. For a moment Haber forgot himself and stared back at those clear, elusive eyes; but only for a moment, so that the strangeness of the experience scarcely registered on his conscious mind.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
